imdb.title: Yôkoso jitsuryoku shijô shugi no kyôshitsu e
imdb.plot: When Kiyotaka enters government-sponsored elite high school, he finds out just how merit-based this education system is.

episodes.title: Remember to keep a clear head in difficult times.
episodes.plot: A new challenge awaits them as a new special exam is to be conducted on ship while this time all classes need to work with each other to win, how will Ayanokoji win this challenge?.

episodes.title: The Material has to be Created
episodes.plot: School is back in session and it's time for the next activity, this time a sports festival splitting the school in two groups. Class D debates on strategies. And we fear there might be a traitor in the near future.

episodes.title: Every Failure Is a Step to Success.
episodes.plot: Ayanokoji's theory that Kushida was a traitor that leaked information that resulted in Class C winning the Cruise Ship test. Interestingly, episode 5 produced more evidence that a traitor in Class 1-D is botching the class's

episodes.title: Adversity Is the First Path to Truth.
episodes.plot: Ayanokouji finally confronts Kushida and manages to make her confess that she has been helping Class C perform better by giving them inside information. Meanwhile, Horikita tries to convince Sudou to not give up and rejoin the class.

episodes.title: To doubt everything or to believe everything are two equally convenient solutions, both dispense with the necessity of reflection.
episodes.plot: After Horikita's brother finally steps down as the President, he passes the baton to another talented student from Class B. The new President vows to bring back meritocracy and ensure that the best talent is rewarded in the school.

episodes.title: The wound is at her heart.
episodes.plot: Things have started to look good for students of Class D. But with the announcement of the next special exam, what new strategy will Ayanokouji come up with to secure more points?

episodes.title: If you make a mistake and do not correct it, this is called a mistake.
episodes.plot: Kushida tries to set up Suzune's expulsion by dealing with Ryuuen.The AYANOKOJI GROUP is created to help out Akito and Hasebe to study while they stumble into Ryuuen who is searching for the mastermind.

episodes.title: People, often deceived by an illusive good, desire their own ruin
episodes.plot: After the meeting with his father, Ayanokoji discovered that Chabashira lied to him to use his intellect to move Class D to Class A. While this deception worked, Ayanokoji, after discovering Chabashira's true intentions.

episodes.title: A man who cannot command himself will always be a slave
episodes.plot: The entire Class 1-D, being concerned about Koenji, followed Ryuuen to the courtyard, where they saw the former being surrounded by the students of Class 1-C. While instigating Koenji, Ryuuen tried to break his things.

episodes.title: Force without wisdom falls of its own weight
episodes.plot: Despite putting Karuizawa through the worst pain imaginable, Ryuuen is still not done as she refuses to give her the mastermind's name. When he even reveals to her that the mastermind has tricked her from the very start.

episodes.title: The worst enemy you can meet will always be yourself
episodes.plot: The aftermath of the gymnasium incident plays out as Christmas brings romance to the school.

episodes.title: What Is Evil? Whatever Springs from Weakness.
episodes.plot: Melancholy, unmotivated Kiyotaka Ayanokouji attends his first day at Tokyo Metropoiltan Advanced Nurturing High School, a government-established institution for training a generation of Japan's best and brightest. In this school, it is said, everything is decided based on merit, which includes the generous monthly "point" allowance students can spend at local shops. As Ayanokouji begins navigating this system, he also nurtures curious relationships with aloof fellow outsider Suzune Horikita and the terminally gregarious Kikyou Kushida.

episodes.title: It Takes a Great Talent and Skill to Conceal One's Talent and Skill.
episodes.plot: 1-D learn more about point system. They need to change their habits if they want to score some. But few students don't want to change even if they are facing expulsion.

episodes.title: Man Is an Animal That Makes Bargains: No Other Animal Does This - No Dog Exchanges Bones with Another.
episodes.plot: Kiyotaka explains to Suzune what he did last three days before test. And why everybody get such good scores on tests. But Sudo failed tests anyway and is going to be expelled.

episodes.title: We Should Not Be Upset That Others Hide the Truth from Us, When We Hide It So Often from Ourselves.
episodes.plot: Classrooms analyze their and others test results. Points distribution is late. Three students from 1-C reported Sudo for attacking them.

episodes.title: Hell Is Other People.
episodes.plot: Kiyotaka and Kushida go with Sakura to he mall where Sakura will try to repair her camera. After that Kiyotaka talk to Sakura about Sado's situation and should she talk about what she saw.

episodes.title: There Are Two Kinds of Lies; One Concerns an Accomplished Fact, the Other Concerns a Future Duty.
episodes.plot: Sakura received some weird messages on her portal, than some pictures of herself. Kiyotaka and Suzune are trying to find evidence that would set Sudo free.

episodes.title: Nothing Is as Dangerous as an Ignorant Friend; a Wise Enemy Is to Be Preferred.
episodes.plot: Kiyotaka convince Suzune to join him and others at the pool.

episodes.title: Abandon All Hope, Ye Who Enter Here.
episodes.plot: All students go to the cruise. Chabashira informs Kiyotaka that somebody requested his expulsion. If he don't help others to promote to A class she will use first opportunity to expel him.

episodes.title: Man Is Condemned to Be Free.
episodes.plot: Survival test starts. Everybody starts with looking for camping sites. 1-D send 3 scout team made from 3 members each.

episodes.title: Every Man Has in Himself the Most Dangerous Traitor of All.
episodes.plot: Second day of survival test starts. Kiyotaka and Suzune go scouting other classes.

episodes.title: What People Commonly Call Fate is Mostly Their Own Stupidity.
episodes.plot: Day 5 of survival test. Girls want to separate from boys. Kiyotaka found out Suzune is being sick from the start.

episodes.title: Genius Lives Only One Story Above Madness.
episodes.plot: Survival test is coming to the end. Things don't look well for 1-D. Key card is stolen. And now Suzune is forced to withdraw due to her sickness. Kiyotaka will try to turn things around.
